13 February 2018 Government wishes to announce the postponement of the Cabinet meeting that was scheduled for this week. The meeting was scheduled to take place on 14 February 2018.  The new date of the Cabinet will be communicated in due cause. Communications Minister Kubayi-Ngubane said “we are alive to the developments taking place in the Ruling Party.  Government   reassures South Africans that service delivery will not be impacted upon”. Enquiries:Phumla WilliamsActing Cabinet SpokespersonMobile: 083 501 0139